p: A total of 105 clusters with at least one new member belonging to the study population was identified. For the five clusters with the highest increase in new members in 2014 and 2016 (respectively 46, 20, 15, 12, and 10 new members), the ratio of early/late diagnosed individuals (18/28, 10/10, 5/10, 6/6, and 8/2) revealed a nearly equal representation.
